<node TEXT="freeGLUT toolkit (alternative for GLUT)" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1516058366" CREATED="1352925659798" MODIFIED="1353186598921"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      A completely Open Source alternative to the OpenGL Utility Toolkit (GLUT) library with an optionally open event loop.
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; text-align: start; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Lucida Grande, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      The<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><b>Free</b><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span>Open<b>GL</b><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><b>U</b>tility<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><b>T</b>oolkit is a cross-platform library for creating and managing an OpenGL window. It abstracts platform-specific code, so code written to use FreeGLUT can work on any platform FreeGLUT supports.
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; text-align: start; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Lucida Grande, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      FreeGLUT is intended for simple graphical demos, and at this purpose, it works quite well. As your needs become more complex, you will run into more and more of FreeGLUT's limitations. Consider<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><b><font color="rgb(70, 101, 162)"><a class="el" style="color: rgb(70, 101, 162); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: initial" href="http://glsdk.sourceforge.net/docs/html/group__module__glfw.html">GLFW</a></font></b><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span>as an alternative if this happens.
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; text-align: start; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Lucida Grande, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      FreeGLUT is distributed under an X-Consortium style license. FreeGLUT maintains<span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><font color="rgb(70, 101, 162)"><a style="color: rgb(70, 101, 162); font-weight: normal; text-decoration: initial" href="http://glsdk.sourceforge.net/freeglut/doc/index.html">separate documentation</a></font>. The SDK uses version 2.6.0
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
