<node TEXT="SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer)" ID="ID_976693366" CREATED="1352854802477" MODIFIED="1353180629470" LINK="http://www.libsdl.org/"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Written in C, it is a cross-platform multimedia library used to present a simple interface and low level access to various platforms' graphics, sound and input devices via OpenGL, and 2D video framebuffer.
    </p>
    <p>
      <font face="sans-serif" size="13px" color="rgb(0, 0, 0)"><span style="font-variant: normal; text-align: left; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.1875px; float: none; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none; display: inline !important">SDL supports Linux, Windows, Windows CE, BeOS, MacOS, Mac OS X, FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD, BSD/OS, Solaris, IRIX, and QNX. The code contains support for AmigaOS, Dreamcast, Atari, AIX, OSF/Tru64, RISC OS, SymbianOS, and OS/2, but these are not officially supported. 1.2 does not support core OpenGL context creation.</span></font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
