  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; padding-right: 0; text-align: start; margin-left: 0px; white-space: normal; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 0; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding-bottom: 0; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      GLM is a C++ mathematics library for graphics software based on the OpenGL Shading Language (GLSL) specification.
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; padding-right: 0; text-align: start; margin-left: 0px; white-space: normal; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 0; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding-bottom: 0; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; padding-right: 0; text-align: start; margin-left: 0px; white-space: normal; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 0; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding-bottom: 0; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      GLM provides classes and functions designed and implemented with the same naming conventions and functionalities than GLSL so that when a programmer knows GLSL, he knows GLM as well which makes it really easy to use.
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; padding-right: 0; text-align: start; margin-left: 0px; white-space: normal; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 0; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding-bottom: 0; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      
    </p>
    <p style="font-variant: normal; padding-right: 0; text-align: start; margin-left: 0px; white-space: normal; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 0; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding-bottom: 0; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none">
      <font face="Lucida Grande, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans-serif" size="12px" color="rgb(0, 0, 0)"><span style="font-variant: normal; text-align: start; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; float: none; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; font-family: Lucida Grande, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; text-transform: none; display: inline !important">This library works perfectly with OpenGL but it also ensures interoperability with third party libraries and SDKs. It is a good candidate for software rendering (Raytracing / Rasterisation), image processing, physic simulations and any context that requires a simple and convenient mathematics library.</span></font>
    </p>
